*Says He Is The Only In APC That Can Defeat Any PDP Candidate UGHELLI – The member representing Ughelli North, Ughelli South, Udu Federal Constituency in the House of Representatives, Reverend Hon. Francis Ejiroghene Waive has called on Vice President Yemi Osinbajo to contest the 2023 Presidential election on the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC). Waive in a press release said he decided to call on the Vice President to contest the 2023 Presidential election because he is the only person that defeat any candidate that the PDP will project. Osun APC To Party’s National Reconciliation Committee:… Fulfill Your Electoral Promises To Us, Ifon-Orolu Community… The Lawmaker who is the Deputy Chairman of the House Committe on Power as well as Chairman Nigeria Niger Parliamentary Friendship Group called on APC leaders to do the needful and support Prof Osinbajo if the party is to win the 2023 Presidential election. He said that the Vice President has displayed all the character traits of a good leader, adding that he has being a trustworthy and loyal deputy to President Mohammedu Buhari. He pointed out that Prof Osinbajo has proven capacity to turn the fortunes of this country around, building on the foundation laid by the present administration. Nigeria he says need a younger leader like Prof Osinbajo who has the presence of mind, vast contacts around the country and respect for the multi ethnic and multi religious dimensions of our country. Prof Osinbajo’s intellectual dept, managerial abilities, patience and tolerance is what our country needs at this crucial time in our history he emphasized. POLL Rev Hon Waive therefore called on all people of goodwill to pray and work for the emergence of Prof Osinbajo as President of Nigeria come 2023.